title: A bachelor's rambles through the British Isles.
author: Butler, Charles J.
snippet: A sixpence, the attendant informed me, would admit me, which amount I paid, and climbed the winding stairway to the balcony, from which I had a good view of the city and surrounding country. The Hill of Howth, the Irish Sea, the Wicklow Mountains, the beautiful country, and most of the city was scenery that I considered very fine. On returning from the monument to the Y. M. C.
